description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the speciality of Gastroenterology. The successful applicant will be joining a very successful team that has a fantastic culture that endorses all of the Trust Values. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Endoscopy has a dedicated Clinical Educator who will facilitate all of your training requirements and ensure that you have a thorough induction. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant will work closely with specialised members of the MDT such as CNS Liver, CNS IBD, CNS Nutrition and Dieticians specialising in Gastro patients and especially with the Bowel Cancer Screening Service. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Endoscopy offers flexible working to the staff in line with the trust&#39;s flexible working policy. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Endoscopy is now one of the most exciting areas to work within the Trust due to the variable nature of the role and furthermore training will be provided in line with JAG - JETS accredited workforce criteria. Staff receive training on a weekly basis from either a specialist nurse or from an outside company to ensure that we are working to the most up to date standards. The successful applicant will work on their own initiative and also as part of a wider team. So if this opportunity appeals to you and you have a passion for the specialised area of Gastroenterolgy, then this could be the position for you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDaniel HobbyJob titleEndoscopy Unit ManagerEmail addressdaniel.hobby@uhnm.nhs.ukTelephone number01782 675706&lt;/p&gt;
